# Proxy OG share-card requests to the dedicated og.tightropetracker.uk Worker.
# Social scrapers (Twitter, Facebook, Slack, etc.) resolve the og:image URL on
# the page's origin. Without this rewrite, unfurls would 404 because the OG
# Worker lives on a different subdomain. A 200 status (rewrite, not redirect)
# keeps the URL stable for consumers while fetching bytes from the Worker.
/og/*  https://og.tightropetracker.uk/:splat  200
